* Opal 2.3 release
  * Removal of number of CPUs for non-parallel jobs on input form: X
  * PBS support (with or without DRMAA)
  * Support upload of tarballs for inputs: X
  * Support for user email as an optional argument: X
  * Modification of jobID to include service name: X
  * Addition of utility services (addition to WSDL)
    * Server load, queue length, data lifetime, server information
  * Addition of the above statistics to the Dashboard
  * Refreshed look and feel for Opal dashboard: X
  * Bug fix for destroy() operation, where baseURL was incorrectly
    returned as empty after job destruction: X
  * Bug fix for IP limits where the query for filtering by IP was incorrect: X
  * Bug fix for SOAP filter to support large files and for empty arguments (X)

* Opal MetaService - submission of jobs to other Opal servers

* REST support - and upgrade to Axis2

* Updated Ajax-based automatic interface generation

* Security enhancements
  * FacebookConnect or OpenID

* Plug-ins
  * Hadoop/EC2 MapReduce plugin

* Performance improvements
  * Ability to queue jobs before job submission - based on an upper bound
    specified in opal.properties
  * Improved fault tolerance on server restarts - being able to bind to
    already running jobs

* WSDL additions/improvements
  * Add GridFTP support
  * Additional statistics for job to be set by client (like email address)
    * Twitter, RSS access to job metadata
  * launchJob should allow the user to specify the wallclock time
  * Support for array jobs

* Additional Features
  * Conditional display of parameters (a group of parameters are displayed only
    if a flag is checked) (reuqested by the PDB guys)
    * Will need addition of relations to parameter types
  * Addition of version number in the application configuration
  * Dashboard should be able to connect to multiple Opal servers
  * Get the version of the Opal server
    * And applications as well
  * Parameterize port numbers for dashboard
  * Addition of implicit files to dashboard 

* Dashboard updates
  * update navigation bar layout 
  * enable navigation bar round corners without image files
  * add coyuright to all pages
  * move all documentation liks to one page
  * enable sorted applications list upon first page load
  * move application usage info into a "row expander"
  * add "Help" tooltip for novice users navigation
  * stop page refresh when job is finished. The default refresh rate is set to 30 sec.
  * Add time stamp for page refreshing.

